<content type="html" xml:base="http://www.classicshell.net/forum/viewtopic.php?t=8052&amp;p=34812#p34812"><![CDATA[
Since uninstalling Classic Shell doesn't solve your problem, it is very likely something got messed up in Windows itself.<br />You need to register StartMenuHelper64.dll if you are using 64-bit Windows.<br />ClassicStartMenuDLL.dll is not a COM DLL, so it doesn't need registration.<p>Statistics: Posted by <a href="http://www.classicshell.net/forum/memberlist.php?mode=viewprofile&amp;u=2">Ivo</a> — Fri Nov 24, 2017 12:17 pm</p><hr />
]]></content>
</entry>
